cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Specter-Tree: TypeScript Code Navigation MCP Server for AI Agents"
abstract: "An open-source Model Context Protocol (MCP) server that gives AI coding agents structural awareness of TypeScript codebases. Agents find any symbol, trace callers, resolve barrel exports, and map class hierarchies by name — without reading whole files. This reduces navigation token usage by 54–67% per session. Works with Claude Code, Cursor, and Codex CLI."
keywords:
  - MCP server
  - TypeScript
  - token optimization
  - Claude Code
  - Cursor
  - Codex CLI
  - AI agent
  - code navigation
  - model context protocol
  - reduce LLM tokens
  - codebase intelligence
  - symbol search
  - AST
  - developer tools
repository-code: "https://github.com/DinoQuinten/specter-tree"
